## 3 · Understanding Natural Language

Map the user's words to the right command. When ambiguous, **ask one
short clarifying question** — don't guess.

### Reads

| User says (examples)                                                 | Command                                    | Notes                                                            |
| -------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| "What am I working on?" / "my tasks" / "what's assigned to me?"      | `my`                                       | Default 20, sorted by priority                                   |
| "Show the sprint" / "sprint board" / "what's in the current sprint?" | `sprint`                                   | Check cache first                                                |
| "Tell me about KEY-249" / "open KEY-249" / "details on 249"          | `get KEY-249`                              | If they omit the project prefix, prepend from `JIRA_PROJECT_KEY` |
| "Show KEY-1, KEY-2, and KEY-3"                                       | `batch KEY-1 KEY-2 KEY-3`                  | Always batch, never loop `get`                                   |
| "What are the subtasks of KEY-100?" / "break down KEY-100"           | `subtasks KEY-100`                         |                                                                  |
| "Find issues about authentication"                                   | `search "summary ~ 'authentication' …"`    | Build JQL for them                                               |
| "Who am I in Jira?"                                                  | `me`                                       | Show display name, not accountId                                 |
| "Recent docs" / "latest wiki pages"                                  | `recent`                                   | Confluence recent pages                                          |
| "My morning update"                                                  | `my --limit 10` then `sprint` (from cache) | Combo workflow                                                   |

### Writes (always confirm first — see §5)

| User says (examples)                                       | Command                                                             | Notes                               |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| "Assign KEY-1 to Sarah"                                    | Look up Sarah's accountId via `find-user`, then `assign KEY-1 <id>` | Never ask the user for an accountId |
| "Move KEY-249 to In Progress" / "start KEY-249"            | `transition KEY-249 "In Progress"`                                  |                                     |
| "Mark KEY-249 as done" / "close KEY-249"                   | `transition KEY-249 "Done"`                                         |                                     |
| "Send KEY-249 to review"                                   | `transition KEY-249 "Ready for Review"`                             |                                     |
| "Create a subtask under KEY-100 called 'Write unit tests'" | `create-subtask KEY-100 "Write unit tests"`                         |                                     |
| "Add a comment on KEY-249: 'Blocked by API changes'"       | `comment KEY-249 "Blocked by API changes"`                          |                                     |
| "Change the summary of KEY-249 to '…'"                     | `update KEY-249 '{"summary":"…"}'`                                  |                                     |
| "Create a new task: 'Set up staging environment'"          | `create "Set up staging environment"`                               | Top-level issue creation            |

### Confluence

| User says (examples)                                       | Command                          | Notes                 |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| "Show me recent docs" / "what's been updated on the wiki?" | `recent`                         |                       |
| "Find the doc about QA test plan"                          | `conf-search "QA test plan"`     | Uses CQL search       |
| "Link me to the standup notes"                             | Known page — provide direct link | See §7 known pages    |
| "What Confluence spaces do we have?"                       | `spaces`                         | List available spaces |

